Procedure.description:
PROCEDURE PURPOSE: to execute MTG-I SKM manoeuvre
PROCEDURE VERSION: 3.0 RESPONSIBILITY: Arturo Del Foco LAST MODIFIED DATE: 21.03.2023
CHANGE HISTORY: Version 3.0 (AdF - 21.03.2023) Change History: - Copied from FOM procedure N_SAT_I150 Version 4 - 31/08/2022 - Procedure Description field updated according to EUMETSAT template; - Procedure History erased and restarted from version 2.0 (first EUM version); - Steps executing PF activities (P.2/P.3/P.4/P.6 of FOM procedure v.4) replaced by a call to EUM version of N_SAT_I150 (which was updated to manage PF activities only - no PL); - GeoSAR management removed, as per PST recommendation provided via email by ESA (Alex Palacios), on Thursday 16 March 2023 09:43, Subject: RE: GeoSAR transponder gain change for SK manoeuvres; - Introduced IF steps to execute PL re-activation only if needed: no action if PL is in Wait or lower macro-mode at the start of this procedure; - Introduced variables to record the PL status at the start of the procedure, in order to restore it after the SK manoeuvre execution; - FCI to Wait procedure: call to N_SAT_I510 replaced by call to N_FCI_I205; - FCI to Observation procedure: call to N_SAT_I500 replaced by call to N_FCI_I800; - Added procedure arguments to populate N_FCI_I800 from parent procedure N_SAT_I810; - Added procedure argument Manoeuvre to populate the manopeuvre type in child procedure N_SAT_I150.
PROCEDURE OBJECTIVES: This procedure is used to execute all the activities foreseen for a Station Keeping manoeuvre (EW, NS or RWOL), including PL management if required.
PROCEDURE OVERVIEW: - check the Pre-conditions applicable to MTG-I satellites prior to the execution of the Station Keeping manoeuver - if in Observation macro-mode, command the FCI and LI to Wait macro-mode - execute the Station Keeping manoeuver - if in Observation mode at the start of this procedure, command the FCI and LI from Wait to Observation macro-mode
PROCEDURE PRE-CONDITIONS: The satellite is in NOM/FPM or SBM/FPM
PROCEDURE CONSTRAINTS All TCs existing in the MTL at the beginning of execution of the procedure are deleted. A pre-condition check informs the Operator if there MTL is not empty at the start of the procedure.
SPACECRAFT CONFIGURATION Start of Procedure: - SAT mode: NOM or SBM - AOCS mode: FPM - AOCS S/S: nominal configuration for FPM - DHS S/S: nominal configuration - TTC S/S: nominal configuration - EPS S/S: nominal configuration - PDD S/S: any - TCS S/S: nominal configuration - UPS S/S: nominal configuration - FCI mode: any - LI mode: any
End of Procedure: - SAT mode: NOM or SBM - AOCS mode: FPM - AOCS S/S: nominal configuration for FPM - DHS S/S: nominal configuration - TTC S/S: nominal configuration - EPS S/S: nominal configuration - PDD S/S: as at procedure start - TCS S/S: nominal configuration - UPS S/S: nominal configuration - FCI mode: as at procedure start - LI mode: as at procedure start
GROUND SEGMENT CONFIGURATION: N/A
